1
00:00:04,104 --> 00:00:06,984
This must be the consequence
of wishing on a shooting star.

2
00:00:09,242 --> 00:00:11,471
Everyone will forget about me.

3
00:00:12,412 --> 00:00:14,943
They'll forget everything about He Xiang Yong.

4
00:00:29,596 --> 00:00:31,231
Hao Wei.

5
00:00:31,231 --> 00:00:32,932
It's you.

6
00:00:32,932 --> 00:00:34,534
Out for a run?

7
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:35,735
Good morning, Mr. Hua.

8
00:00:35,735 --> 00:00:37,269
Hello.

9
00:00:38,738 --> 00:00:41,508
Mr. Hua, I wanted to ask you,

10
00:00:41,508 --> 00:00:43,109
how long have you lived on this island?

11
00:00:43,109 --> 00:00:44,411
Over ten years now. Why do you ask?

12
00:00:44,411 --> 00:00:45,762
-

13
00:00:49,816 --> 00:00:52,419
Tell me, on this island,

14
00:00:52,419 --> 00:00:55,021
is the legend about wishing
on shooting stars actually true?

15
00:01:43,036 --> 00:01:44,338
One more, okay?

16
00:01:44,338 --> 00:01:46,671
Du Du, come here. One more.

17
00:01:46,671 --> 00:01:47,239
-

18
00:01:50,343 --> 00:01:51,911
Good morning, Mr. He.

19
00:01:51,911 --> 00:01:54,214
- Good morning.
- Why are you sitting here so early?

20
00:01:54,214 --> 00:01:55,615
Xiao You woke me up early,
saying he wanted to make me breakfast.

21
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:56,950
-

22
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:59,520
Try some of my fish porridge.

23
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:01,920
Fish porridge is quite complex.
How do you know how to make it?

24
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,689
-

25
00:02:02,689 --> 00:02:04,257
It's not that complicated.

26
00:02:04,257 --> 00:02:06,225
I used to make it often.

27
00:02:08,061 --> 00:02:11,798
My dad used to say that
to sober up in the morning,

28
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:13,867
fish porridge is the only way.

29
00:02:13,867 --> 00:02:15,102
Your dad is an expert. Just like me.

30
00:02:15,102 --> 00:02:16,135
-

31
00:02:16,135 --> 00:02:19,304
I also like to have some fish porridge after a night of drinking.

32
00:02:19,304 --> 00:02:19,805
-

33
00:02:20,907 --> 00:02:22,642
- Here, Mr. He.
- Wait a minute.

34
00:02:22,642 --> 00:02:25,082
So, you two were drinking
behind my back last night?

35
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:28,281
We'll invite you next time.

36
00:02:28,281 --> 00:02:30,049
Try my fish porridge first.

37
00:02:30,049 --> 00:02:32,685
How rude.

38
00:02:32,685 --> 00:02:34,419
- Thank you.
- Du Du, come here.

39
00:02:38,057 --> 00:02:39,483
Thank you.

40
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:47,167
This is incredibly delicious.

41
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:49,567
Of course it is.
It's my family's secret recipe.

42
00:02:49,567 --> 00:02:50,170
-

43
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,985
You could open a shop with this.

44
00:02:57,644 --> 00:03:00,124
What's wrong? Is it not to your taste?

45
00:03:02,148 --> 00:03:04,250
It's delicious.

46
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:07,119
I feel like I've tasted this somewhere before.

47
00:03:09,756 --> 00:03:11,457
I'm glad you like it.

48
00:03:11,457 --> 00:03:13,660
If you ever want to eat it again,
just let me know.

49
00:03:13,660 --> 00:03:15,627
I'll make it for you.

50
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,869
Mr. He, would you like an egg?

51
00:03:22,869 --> 00:03:24,129
Thank you.

52
00:03:25,939 --> 00:03:27,158
Thank you.

53
00:03:28,808 --> 00:03:30,060
Eat up.

54
00:03:34,914 --> 00:03:37,550
But I think this fish porridge

55
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:40,687
still has room for improvement.

56
00:03:40,687 --> 00:03:42,589
I'll take you somewhere tomorrow.

57
00:03:42,589 --> 00:03:45,089
I'll show you how to upgrade it.

58
00:03:51,998 --> 00:03:54,067
Du Du, come here.

59
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,835
It's good. Give it a try.

60
00:03:55,835 --> 00:03:57,469
Good boy.

61
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:25,365
Hamaguchi Aomi! Time to wake up.

62
00:04:25,365 --> 00:04:26,633
-

63
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:28,167
Wake up!

64
00:04:28,167 --> 00:04:29,335
Hamaguchi Aomi! Time to wake up.

65
00:04:29,335 --> 00:04:30,837
-

66
00:04:30,837 --> 00:04:32,805
Hamaguchi Aomi!

67
00:04:33,539 --> 00:04:36,874
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

68
00:04:36,874 --> 00:04:37,276
-

69
00:04:38,077 --> 00:04:41,948
Can you help me call Hama-chan?

70
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:43,716
Okay.

71
00:04:43,716 --> 00:04:45,584
Thank you.

72
00:04:55,395 --> 00:04:57,463
Li Wan Zhe.

73
00:04:57,463 --> 00:04:59,165
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

74
00:04:59,165 --> 00:05:01,601
You're here early.

75
00:05:01,601 --> 00:05:03,336
Can you take the day off today?

76
00:05:03,336 --> 00:05:04,470
Why?

77
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:06,706
Come with me to the main island.

78
00:05:06,706 --> 00:05:07,740
What for?

79
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:10,141
Don't ask so many questions.
Are you coming or not?

80
00:05:10,141 --> 00:05:11,044
-

81
00:05:11,044 --> 00:05:12,845
No way. Go home and rest.

82
00:05:12,845 --> 00:05:13,713
-

83
00:05:13,713 --> 00:05:15,014
Get some sleep.

84
00:05:15,014 --> 00:05:17,917
No, it has to be today.

85
00:05:17,917 --> 00:05:19,528
Hey!

86
00:05:22,488 --> 00:05:25,291
Hama-chan, stop sleeping!

87
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:27,226
Do you know what time it is?

88
00:05:27,226 --> 00:05:30,530
I've had enough sleep. Wake up, Hamaguchi Aomi!

89
00:05:30,530 --> 00:05:32,332
Hamaguchi Aomi!

90
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:34,367
Hamaguchi...

91
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:36,269
What time is it? Don't I need to sleep?

92
00:05:36,269 --> 00:05:38,563
Stop sleeping, Mr. Ying.

93
00:05:38,563 --> 00:05:40,873
- That hurts!
- Get out!

94
00:05:42,475 --> 00:05:44,143
Keep your voice down!

95
00:05:44,143 --> 00:05:46,879
No, I'm going to be loud.

96
00:05:46,879 --> 00:05:48,081
Hamaguchi Aomi.

97
00:05:48,081 --> 00:05:50,249
Born on January 10, 1998.

98
00:05:50,249 --> 00:05:51,417
Capricorn.

99
00:05:51,417 --> 00:05:52,685
Blood type AB.

100
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:54,253
Your favorite food is plums.

101
00:05:54,253 --> 00:05:56,089
You hate mushrooms.

102
00:05:56,089 --> 00:05:57,390
Your dream is to travel the world.
You want to go to Antarctica.

103
00:05:57,390 --> 00:05:58,391
-

104
00:05:58,391 --> 00:06:00,393
And you said I was your whole world.

105
00:06:00,393 --> 00:06:02,227
Your whole world?

106
00:06:02,895 --> 00:06:05,797
You also said you liked me most
because of how filial I am to my family.

107
00:06:05,797 --> 00:06:06,332
-

108
00:06:06,332 --> 00:06:08,333
You like my cute eyes and my tall nose.

109
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:09,035
-

110
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:11,037
You used to buy me lots of treats.

111
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:13,439
You even helped me get concert tickets.

112
00:06:13,439 --> 00:06:15,542
You even fought others for me.

113
00:06:15,542 --> 00:06:18,042
And you...
You even took my first kiss.

114
00:06:18,042 --> 00:06:18,911
-

115
00:06:19,946 --> 00:06:21,514
Stop talking nonsense.

116
00:06:21,514 --> 00:06:23,549
I'm not talking nonsense.

117
00:06:23,549 --> 00:06:25,718
We really went through a lot together.

118
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:27,286
But I don't know why you've forgotten everything.

119
00:06:27,286 --> 00:06:28,187
-

120
00:06:28,187 --> 00:06:31,189
I really hope you can celebrate my birthday with me.

121
00:06:31,189 --> 00:06:31,924
-

122
00:06:31,924 --> 00:06:34,092
And do all those things we never got to finish.

123
00:06:34,092 --> 00:06:34,927
-

124
00:06:34,927 --> 00:06:37,162
Please.

125
00:06:37,764 --> 00:06:39,399
Fine, just go.

126
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:41,801
I'll ask the captain for your leave.

127
00:06:41,801 --> 00:06:44,537
All right, I'm going back to sleep.

128
00:06:44,537 --> 00:06:45,605
Go on.

129
00:06:45,605 --> 00:06:47,273
You go. I'm going to sleep.

130
00:06:47,273 --> 00:06:48,754
So noisy.

131
00:06:52,645 --> 00:06:53,813
Okay.

132
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:55,514
Wait for me.

133
00:07:00,052 --> 00:07:01,820
Hurry up.

134
00:07:08,694 --> 00:07:10,530
Buy fish based on what you're cooking.

135
00:07:10,530 --> 00:07:12,932
If you want to make a big feast
with those large deep-sea fish

136
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:13,666
-

137
00:07:13,666 --> 00:07:15,101
go over there.

138
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:18,436
If you want home-cooked food to fry, boil, or sauté this is the right place.

139
00:07:18,436 --> 00:07:19,204
-

140
00:07:19,204 --> 00:07:19,839
-

141
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:21,574
Hey, kids.

142
00:07:21,574 --> 00:07:23,009
Playing with ice? Aren't you cold?

143
00:07:23,009 --> 00:07:24,644
- Li!
- Hi!

144
00:07:24,644 --> 00:07:25,778
Hello.

145
00:07:25,778 --> 00:07:27,780
- I'm buying fish.
- Okay.

146
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:29,515
Do you know how to pick fish?

147
00:07:29,515 --> 00:07:30,960
No.

148
00:07:32,051 --> 00:07:33,786
Take a look.

149
00:07:33,786 --> 00:07:36,055
Look at this one.

150
00:07:36,055 --> 00:07:38,724
When buying fish, look at the eyes first.

151
00:07:38,724 --> 00:07:41,994
The eyes should be nice and shiny.

152
00:07:41,994 --> 00:07:44,330
The gills must be bright red.

153
00:07:44,330 --> 00:07:46,532
The scales must be intact.

154
00:07:46,532 --> 00:07:47,400
-

155
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,235
Squeeze the belly.

156
00:07:49,235 --> 00:07:51,737
It should be firm and elastic.

157
00:07:51,737 --> 00:07:54,240
Smell it. Is there any odor?

158
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:56,108
- No.
- If not, then buy it.

159
00:07:56,108 --> 00:07:57,443
- Li, I'll take this one.
- Okay.

160
00:07:57,443 --> 00:07:58,878
Clean it for me. I'll pick it up later.

161
00:07:58,878 --> 00:08:00,479
Okay.

162
00:08:03,082 --> 00:08:04,484
Boss, what's fresh today?

163
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:06,752
We have salmon heads,
shrimp, and yellow croaker.

164
00:08:06,752 --> 00:08:09,555
- These shrimp are huge.
- The salmon heads are beautiful.

165
00:08:09,555 --> 00:08:11,457
- Take a look.
- See?

166
00:08:11,457 --> 00:08:13,658
- Bright red. Do you see?
- They're gorgeous.

167
00:08:13,658 --> 00:08:14,293
-

168
00:08:14,293 --> 00:08:16,828
I'll keep looking. Thank you.

169
00:08:16,828 --> 00:08:17,429
-

170
00:08:19,398 --> 00:08:21,906
This must be your first time
at a fish market like this.

171
00:08:23,469 --> 00:08:27,105
My dad used to ask me to join him, but I always said no.

172
00:08:27,105 --> 00:08:28,007
-

173
00:08:28,007 --> 00:08:30,709
After a few times, he stopped asking.

174
00:08:31,544 --> 00:08:35,147
Now, I wish I could go with him every day.

175
00:08:35,147 --> 00:08:37,482
If you want to, then do it.

176
00:08:37,482 --> 00:08:40,719
If you just keep thinking about it,
it'll never happen.

177
00:08:45,291 --> 00:08:47,759
You must have had a fight with your dad.

178
00:08:49,195 --> 00:08:51,196
Not exactly.

179
00:08:52,164 --> 00:08:54,634
But we used to argue a lot.

180
00:08:54,634 --> 00:08:57,770
Our personalities are too similar.

181
00:08:57,770 --> 00:09:00,672
We clearly care about each other,
but we're both too proud to admit it.

182
00:09:00,672 --> 00:09:01,306
-

183
00:09:06,579 --> 00:09:08,681
Your dad has already let go of his pride.

184
00:09:08,681 --> 00:09:10,916
You just haven't realized it yet.

185
00:09:13,786 --> 00:09:15,721
Didn't he invite you to the fish market?

186
00:09:15,721 --> 00:09:18,958
He's trying to bridge the gap between you.

187
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:23,329
Sometimes, men don't say much.

188
00:09:23,329 --> 00:09:25,698
He brought you to the place he knows best

189
00:09:25,698 --> 00:09:28,055
because he wants you to understand him.

190
00:09:30,269 --> 00:09:33,404
Maybe he just wants you to see the words written up there.

191
00:09:33,404 --> 00:09:34,164
-

192
00:09:34,164 --> 00:09:35,019
-

193
00:09:35,019 --> 00:09:37,577
[Be careful not to slip]

194
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:39,172
What do you mean?

195
00:09:42,882 --> 00:09:44,750
When you were learning to walk,
your dad must have stayed by your side.

196
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:45,952
-

197
00:09:45,952 --> 00:09:47,687
He was afraid you'd get hurt.

198
00:09:47,687 --> 00:09:51,722
Now that you're grown up,
you have your own path to walk.

199
00:09:51,722 --> 00:09:52,458
-

200
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:56,326
You don't need him to accompany you,
but he's still afraid you'll get hurt.

201
00:09:56,326 --> 00:09:57,062
-

202
00:10:01,701 --> 00:10:03,789
It's because I'm not good enough.

203
00:10:04,804 --> 00:10:07,027
I always disappoint him.

204
00:10:11,477 --> 00:10:13,311
What makes you "not good enough"?

205
00:10:15,715 --> 00:10:17,816
What does being "good" even mean?

206
00:10:20,753 --> 00:10:24,123
When it comes to family,
we just want everyone to be

207
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:28,527
safe and healthy, and to love one another.

208
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:33,399
Let me tell you, go back and tell your dad,

209
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:34,967
"I love you."

210
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:37,737
I'm telling you, he'll be so thrilled,

211
00:10:37,737 --> 00:10:38,938
he'll feel like a total success.

212
00:10:38,938 --> 00:10:40,239
He might even run for village chief tomorrow.

213
00:10:40,239 --> 00:10:41,841
I'm serious.

214
00:10:41,841 --> 00:10:43,776
Li, is my fish ready?

215
00:10:43,776 --> 00:10:44,977
It's ready.

216
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:46,551
Dad,

217
00:10:47,947 --> 00:10:49,283
I love you.

218
00:10:49,283 --> 00:10:50,315
Go tell your dad that.

219
00:10:50,315 --> 00:10:51,584
Why are you telling me?

220
00:10:51,584 --> 00:10:53,185
How much?

221
00:10:53,185 --> 00:10:54,877
Two hundred. Here you go.

222
00:10:56,055 --> 00:10:57,823
Okay, thank you.

223
00:10:57,823 --> 00:11:00,559
Just let me practice a bit.

224
00:11:00,559 --> 00:11:02,395
- I love you!
- Stop it already.

225
00:11:02,395 --> 00:11:03,596
You're giving me goosebumps.

226
00:11:03,596 --> 00:11:05,731
Here, two hundred. Li, he says he loves you!

227
00:11:05,731 --> 00:11:07,333
Go tell her yourself.

228
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,801
Kids, bye-bye!

229
00:11:08,801 --> 00:11:09,969
Bye! Come again soon.

230
00:11:09,969 --> 00:11:11,637
Okay, see you next time.

231
00:11:11,637 --> 00:11:12,872
You guys are the best.

232
00:11:12,872 --> 00:11:14,273
I didn't expect the fish market to be so small.

233
00:11:14,273 --> 00:11:16,174
Why are there so few people?

234
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:45,771
What are you looking for?

235
00:11:45,771 --> 00:11:46,906
I can help you find it.

236
00:11:46,906 --> 00:11:49,408
I'm looking for Chocola BB Plus.

237
00:11:49,408 --> 00:11:50,976
My mom specifically told me that
since I'm on the main island,

238
00:11:50,976 --> 00:11:52,578
I have to buy it for her.

239
00:11:52,578 --> 00:11:54,880
Why did she specify this one?

240
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:58,551
She said it's a popular product
imported from Japan.

241
00:11:58,551 --> 00:12:00,453
It has a Vitamin B complex formula.

242
00:12:00,453 --> 00:12:02,788
Vitamins B2, B6, and B1.

243
00:12:02,788 --> 00:12:04,657
It provides nutritional support
to maintain health.

244
00:12:04,657 --> 00:12:05,858
The key is that the tablets are small.

245
00:12:05,858 --> 00:12:07,793
They're super easy to swallow.

246
00:12:07,793 --> 00:12:10,362
My mom also said
it's made by a famous Japanese brand.

247
00:12:10,362 --> 00:12:11,697
The quality is guaranteed.

248
00:12:11,697 --> 00:12:13,165
She's been taking it every day lately.

249
00:12:13,165 --> 00:12:14,600
It gives her a healthy glow.

250
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,668
She even told me to take it, too.

251
00:12:15,668 --> 00:12:18,471
She said we should take care
of ourselves anytime, anywhere.

252
00:12:18,471 --> 00:12:19,638
But...

253
00:12:19,638 --> 00:12:21,841
I think you should take it, too.

254
00:12:21,841 --> 00:12:23,000
Me?

255
00:12:23,876 --> 00:12:25,511
Why?

256
00:12:25,511 --> 00:12:28,814
Well, you've been so busy lately.

257
00:12:28,814 --> 00:12:31,950
You look a bit worn out.

258
00:12:33,152 --> 00:12:34,954
Are you criticizing my looks?

259
00:12:34,954 --> 00:12:36,288
I'm not criticizing you.

260
00:12:36,288 --> 00:12:38,323
I'm caring for you.

261
00:12:46,866 --> 00:12:48,601
I get it.

262
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,202
This is your way of hitting on me.

263
00:12:50,202 --> 00:12:51,871
Yeah, right!

264
00:12:51,871 --> 00:12:53,739
Let me give you some honest advice.

265
00:12:53,739 --> 00:12:55,341
Try a more normal move.

266
00:12:55,341 --> 00:12:57,275
I'm not hitting on you.

267
00:12:58,144 --> 00:12:59,678
I'm not hitting on you.

268
00:12:59,678 --> 00:13:02,381
I'm helping you regain the memory of liking me.

269
00:13:02,381 --> 00:13:04,049
But right now, it sounds like...

270
00:13:04,049 --> 00:13:06,886
you're the one who likes me.

271
00:13:06,886 --> 00:13:09,288
It's only because you were so persistent,
your devotion moved the heavens.

272
00:13:09,288 --> 00:13:10,689
I was only touched by you
and then fell for you.

273
00:13:10,689 --> 00:13:12,458
I get it.

274
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:14,293
Whatever you say.

275
00:13:14,293 --> 00:13:15,995
Hamaguchi Aomi.

276
00:13:15,995 --> 00:13:18,164
You little rascal.

277
00:13:18,164 --> 00:13:20,599
Hama-chan. What are you laughing at?

278
00:13:20,599 --> 00:13:22,835
I didn't expect you to shop
at Matsumoto Kiyoshi, too.

279
00:13:22,835 --> 00:13:23,869
Of course I do.

280
00:13:23,869 --> 00:13:25,337
It's a famous Japanese drugstore.

281
00:13:25,337 --> 00:13:27,339
Do you think I'm a country bumpkin?

282
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:36,481
Then do you know about this?

283
00:13:37,349 --> 00:13:40,218
Their store brand is cheap and good.

284
00:13:43,088 --> 00:13:44,723
Of course I know.

285
00:13:44,723 --> 00:13:47,805
Listen, I've tried everything here before.

286
00:13:55,668 --> 00:13:57,047
Look at this one.

287
00:13:58,137 --> 00:14:00,171
It's so cute.

288
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:04,115
Shopping with you provides
zero emotional value.

289
00:14:05,477 --> 00:14:06,879
This one actually suits you.

290
00:14:06,879 --> 00:14:09,348
- Does it look good?
- Not bad.

291
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:11,016
Let's go.

292
00:14:15,988 --> 00:14:18,757
Why the long face while shopping?

293
00:14:20,559 --> 00:14:22,227
It looks good, right?

294
00:14:36,275 --> 00:14:38,410
Look, sausages. Sausage with sticky rice.

295
00:14:38,410 --> 00:14:40,179
I'm telling you, this is a must-eat.

296
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:42,214
Let's get some sugarcane juice, too.

297
00:14:42,214 --> 00:14:44,282
Sugarcane juice.

298
00:14:45,317 --> 00:14:46,452
Hello.

299
00:14:46,452 --> 00:14:47,820
I'd like the mixed combo.

300
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:49,188
- Okay. Eating it now?
- Yes.

301
00:14:49,188 --> 00:14:51,023
Okay. Here's a fresh one for you.

302
00:14:51,023 --> 00:14:53,592
- It looks so good.
- Okay, thank you.

303
00:14:53,592 --> 00:14:54,593
- Thank you.
- Okay, thank you.

304
00:14:54,593 --> 00:14:55,861
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

305
00:14:55,861 --> 00:14:57,229
There you go. Thank you.

306
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:58,898
Thank you.

307
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:00,799
- Bye-bye.
- Thank you.

308
00:15:00,799 --> 00:15:02,468
Chicken feet. You've never had them?

309
00:15:02,468 --> 00:15:03,969
Chicken feet! Chicken feet.

310
00:15:03,969 --> 00:15:05,971
- Chicken feet.
- He's never had them. He's Japanese.

311
00:15:05,971 --> 00:15:07,873
- He's never tried it.
- Yeah.

312
00:15:07,873 --> 00:15:10,476
- Thank you.
- Come on, smell it.

313
00:15:10,476 --> 00:15:12,099
Hello.

314
00:15:15,281 --> 00:15:16,615
Come on.

315
00:15:16,615 --> 00:15:17,750
What are you saying? I don't understand.

316
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,151
- No, thanks.
- Come on.

317
00:15:19,151 --> 00:15:20,185
It looks ugly.

318
00:15:20,185 --> 00:15:22,788
It's not ugly. You picked out
such cool glasses yourself.

319
00:15:22,788 --> 00:15:24,589
Wait a second.

320
00:15:26,325 --> 00:15:27,778
Be cool.

321
00:15:36,335 --> 00:15:37,836
It's so stinky.

322
00:15:37,836 --> 00:15:40,122
I'm telling you,
the stinkier it is, the tastier.

323
00:15:43,709 --> 00:15:45,677
You have to try a bite.

324
00:15:46,845 --> 00:15:48,646
Come on.

325
00:15:50,516 --> 00:15:52,251
Otherwise, you can have chicken feet.

326
00:15:52,251 --> 00:15:53,952
Chicken feet don't stink.

327
00:15:55,154 --> 00:15:57,055
Why don't you want to try anything?

328
00:15:57,893 --> 00:16:00,659
Xiao Tian, that fish ball shop we just visited!

329
00:16:00,659 --> 00:16:02,261
I've eaten there for ten years,
and the taste hasn't changed.

330
00:16:02,261 --> 00:16:03,829
Yeah, it's impressive.

331
00:16:03,829 --> 00:16:06,564
- It's pretty good.
- Why don't you have a drink then?

332
00:16:13,839 --> 00:16:15,641
What are you looking at?

333
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:18,042
- Just eat your food.
- What's your problem?

334
00:16:18,677 --> 00:16:20,446
Sorry. Sorry about that.

335
00:16:20,446 --> 00:16:22,247
We're tourists visiting for the first time.

336
00:16:22,247 --> 00:16:24,683
And he's Japanese. So, his Chinese...

337
00:16:24,683 --> 00:16:26,218
is really terrible.

338
00:16:26,218 --> 00:16:28,120
But your food is delicious.

339
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,955
I bought so much just now,
I can't finish it all.

340
00:16:29,955 --> 00:16:32,224
Here, it's on us today.

341
00:16:32,224 --> 00:16:33,993
Why are you giving it to them?

342
00:16:33,993 --> 00:16:35,561
Be quiet for a second.

343
00:16:35,561 --> 00:16:37,062
Just be quiet.

344
00:16:37,062 --> 00:16:39,264
Why are we treating them?

345
00:16:39,264 --> 00:16:40,533
Shut up.

346
00:16:40,533 --> 00:16:41,533
Come on, let's go.

347
00:16:41,533 --> 00:16:43,902
Why did you suddenly speak Japanese?

348
00:16:43,902 --> 00:16:45,270
What's going on?

349
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:47,473
Let's go.

350
00:16:47,473 --> 00:16:49,641
Sorry.

351
00:16:49,641 --> 00:16:51,477
Why did you suddenly speak Japanese?

352
00:16:51,477 --> 00:16:53,079
What a little punk.

353
00:16:53,079 --> 00:16:54,546
I just got angry for no reason.

354
00:16:54,546 --> 00:16:56,849
I don't know why,
but he makes me want to hit him.

355
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:59,685
Boss, when I see him, my face starts to hurt.

356
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:00,719
- I don't know why.
- Your face hurts?

357
00:17:00,719 --> 00:17:02,423
I think you're just looking for trouble.

358
00:17:09,294 --> 00:17:11,430
We've eaten everything we should.

359
00:17:11,430 --> 00:17:13,498
We've done everything fun.

360
00:17:14,466 --> 00:17:16,969
So, why did you bring me
to the main island today?

361
00:17:16,969 --> 00:17:18,503
What exactly are you up to?

362
00:17:22,074 --> 00:17:23,908
You want to know?

363
00:17:27,112 --> 00:17:30,113
Then promise me three things first,
and I'll tell you.

364
00:17:39,691 --> 00:17:43,528
First, you must never give up
on your dream of being a sailor.

365
00:17:44,463 --> 00:17:46,398
I would never give up on that anyway.

366
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:48,167
That's good.

367
00:17:48,167 --> 00:17:51,003
Second, no matter what danger you face,

368
00:17:51,003 --> 00:17:52,438
you must protect yourself first

369
00:17:52,438 --> 00:17:54,105
before you can protect me.

370
00:18:00,946 --> 00:18:02,547
Third!

371
00:18:04,183 --> 00:18:05,784
Whenever you hear this bell,

372
00:18:05,784 --> 00:18:07,319
you have to listen to me.

373
00:18:07,319 --> 00:18:09,420
Why this again?

374
00:18:10,355 --> 00:18:11,557
You gave this to me yourself.

375
00:18:11,557 --> 00:18:13,592
You said, as long as I ring this bell,

376
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:14,993
no matter where I am or what time it is,

377
00:18:14,993 --> 00:18:16,795
you'll come and find me.

378
00:18:16,795 --> 00:18:17,963
But then you forgot about it.

379
00:18:17,963 --> 00:18:19,164
Anyway, I'm using this bell now.

380
00:18:19,164 --> 00:18:20,798
Okay.

381
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:23,561
I promise.

382
00:18:24,636 --> 00:18:26,029
Good.

383
00:18:28,907 --> 00:18:31,777
Congratulations, Hamaguchi Aomi.

384
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:33,912
I ate stinky tofu and chicken feet.

385
00:18:33,912 --> 00:18:36,581
- I'm Li Wan Zhe.
- I know.

386
00:18:38,517 --> 00:18:40,419
I know you brought me to the main island

387
00:18:40,419 --> 00:18:42,520
because you wanted to confess to me.

388
00:18:45,591 --> 00:18:50,261
You like me, don't you?

389
00:18:51,864 --> 00:18:54,099
Me, too.

390
00:18:54,099 --> 00:18:56,067
I like you, too.

391
00:18:56,935 --> 00:18:58,703
So...

392
00:18:59,838 --> 00:19:01,639
please date me.

393
00:19:04,276 --> 00:19:05,636
Okay.

394
00:19:07,012 --> 00:19:08,213
I knew it.

395
00:19:08,213 --> 00:19:10,648
You clearly liked me first.

396
00:19:19,191 --> 00:19:20,614
That's it?

397
00:19:26,698 --> 00:19:28,100
I even brought so many props.

398
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:29,134
Look, I even brought this.

399
00:19:29,134 --> 00:19:31,336
It's useless. Look at this.

400
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,071
And this. Honk, honk!

401
00:19:33,071 --> 00:19:34,973
It's gone.

402
00:20:01,466 --> 00:20:03,835
Wait, I'm not done yet!

403
00:20:05,971 --> 00:20:08,607
I even brought sparklers.

404
00:20:08,607 --> 00:20:11,109
I thought if...

405
00:20:11,109 --> 00:20:12,512
If my confession was successful...

406
00:20:12,512 --> 00:20:13,544
Wait, it wasn't my confession.

407
00:20:13,544 --> 00:20:15,080
You're clearly the one who likes me.

408
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:17,015
Yes, you're the one who likes me.

409
00:20:24,756 --> 00:20:27,392
Li Wan Zhe.

410
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:29,894
I like you.

411
00:20:30,996 --> 00:20:33,498
I like you!

412
00:20:39,071 --> 00:20:41,305
It's hot!

413
00:20:42,474 --> 00:20:43,642
Here, take this one.

414
00:20:43,642 --> 00:20:45,978
- Hurry up.
- Don't push it on me.

415
00:20:45,978 --> 00:20:49,447
Draw a circle.

416
00:21:22,442 --> 00:21:24,837
[Home is He-re]

417
00:21:28,854 --> 00:21:30,255
The way you're holding that drill,

418
00:21:30,255 --> 00:21:32,723
I can tell you're an amateur.

419
00:21:34,393 --> 00:21:35,927
It's broken.

420
00:21:35,927 --> 00:21:37,062
No, it's not.

421
00:21:37,062 --> 00:21:38,963
You're drilling in reverse.

422
00:21:40,532 --> 00:21:43,702
I know what I'm doing, okay?

423
00:21:43,702 --> 00:21:44,836
Look, it's going in.

424
00:21:44,836 --> 00:21:45,837
How long are you going to drill for?

425
00:21:45,837 --> 00:21:47,639
I'm going to sleep soon. Don't wake me up.

426
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:49,408
It won't kill you to skip sleep for a day.

427
00:21:49,408 --> 00:21:50,409
I'm going night fishing tonight.

428
00:21:50,409 --> 00:21:51,543
It's very important, you know?

429
00:21:51,543 --> 00:21:53,512
- You can go night fishing any day.
- Hello?

430
00:21:53,512 --> 00:21:54,515
Is anyone here?

431
00:21:54,515 --> 00:21:55,546
- A guest!
- I have a reservation.

432
00:21:55,546 --> 00:21:56,748
Coming!

433
00:21:56,748 --> 00:21:57,983
I'll go.

434
00:21:57,983 --> 00:21:59,817
I'll come back and help you later.

435
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:03,555
Keep it down. There's a guest.
Why are you so loud?

436
00:22:03,555 --> 00:22:04,690
This is just how it sounds.

437
00:22:04,690 --> 00:22:06,725
Excuse me.

438
00:22:06,725 --> 00:22:09,727
Hello, are you checking in?

439
00:22:10,962 --> 00:22:13,097
Chen Hao Wei?

440
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:14,966
Mr. Lin.

441
00:22:14,966 --> 00:22:16,802
What are you doing here?

442
00:22:16,802 --> 00:22:18,370
Did you switch to running an inn?

443
00:22:18,370 --> 00:22:20,339
Investing in real estate?

444
00:22:20,339 --> 00:22:21,406
No, I...

445
00:22:21,406 --> 00:22:22,407
I'm just working here.

446
00:22:22,407 --> 00:22:23,675
Working?

447
00:22:23,675 --> 00:22:26,211
But all my money went down the drain.

448
00:22:26,211 --> 00:22:29,014
So, what do you think?
Do you have any new investment advice?

449
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:30,115
You're my stock market Jonah.

450
00:22:30,115 --> 00:22:31,917
My inverse indicator.

451
00:22:31,917 --> 00:22:35,288
Thanks to you,
I finally have time to come fishing.

452
00:22:35,288 --> 00:22:36,321
Come on, tell me.

453
00:22:36,321 --> 00:22:37,989
Since you ruined me anyway,

454
00:22:37,989 --> 00:22:39,091
and I had to close my company.

455
00:22:39,091 --> 00:22:40,392
Let me get you checked in first.

456
00:22:40,392 --> 00:22:41,426
Thank you.

457
00:22:41,426 --> 00:22:44,662
You made me realize wealth
is just a worldly possession.

458
00:22:45,263 --> 00:22:48,867
Come on. Tell me about some new investments.

459
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:50,836
Chen Hao Wei.

460
00:22:50,836 --> 00:22:51,937
Didn't I tell you to go buy things?

461
00:22:51,937 --> 00:22:54,339
Why are you just standing here?

462
00:22:54,339 --> 00:22:57,076
Sir? Are you checking in?

463
00:22:57,076 --> 00:22:58,076
Wow, look at this fishing rod.

464
00:22:58,076 --> 00:22:59,076
You like fishing too?

465
00:22:59,076 --> 00:23:00,379
I'm just a beginner.

466
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:01,480
I didn't use to fish.

467
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,048
A beginner? You've come to the right place.

468
00:23:03,048 --> 00:23:04,716
Our boss is a pro at fishing.

469
00:23:04,716 --> 00:23:05,851
Boss!

470
00:23:05,851 --> 00:23:08,120
- Boss!
- What is it?

471
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:10,255
This gentleman loves fishing, too.

472
00:23:10,255 --> 00:23:12,891
Why don't you two talk shop?

473
00:23:12,891 --> 00:23:14,059
You like fishing, sir?

474
00:23:14,059 --> 00:23:16,461
I know a thing or two.

475
00:23:16,461 --> 00:23:18,330
- Our boss is amazing.
- This is a great rod.

476
00:23:18,330 --> 00:23:20,432
Of course it is. It cost me three houses.

477
00:23:20,432 --> 00:23:22,501
- That expensive?
- All thanks to my good employee.

478
00:23:22,501 --> 00:23:23,568
Come on, let's get you checked in.

479
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:24,836
Let's register inside. Thank you.

480
00:23:24,836 --> 00:23:26,438
- I'll take that for you.
- Let's go buy the bait.

481
00:23:26,438 --> 00:23:28,673
All right, go on.

482
00:23:28,673 --> 00:23:29,808
Let me tell you.

483
00:23:29,808 --> 00:23:31,009
Here on Starry Islet,

484
00:23:31,009 --> 00:23:33,311
you don't even need hooks to fish.

485
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:50,762
That Mr. Lin...

486
00:23:50,762 --> 00:23:53,489
He must be the client
who lost everything because of you.

487
00:24:05,444 --> 00:24:08,746
Do you know why the sea is blue?

488
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:13,852
I don't know.

489
00:24:13,852 --> 00:24:15,854
Because the fish in the sea...

490
00:24:15,854 --> 00:24:18,623
Go "blue, blue, blue."

491
00:24:22,260 --> 00:24:24,595
Blue, blue, blue...

492
00:24:29,534 --> 00:24:32,136
Is it that funny?

493
00:24:39,778 --> 00:24:41,512
See?

494
00:24:42,347 --> 00:24:44,583
Since you can laugh,

495
00:24:44,583 --> 00:24:49,421
you should also remember
to be angry, and to be sad.

496
00:24:49,421 --> 00:24:51,690
Cry when you want to cry,

497
00:24:51,690 --> 00:24:54,392
and laugh when you want to laugh.

498
00:24:54,392 --> 00:24:56,794
We aren't robots.

499
00:24:58,997 --> 00:25:02,800
With me, you don't need to hide who you are.

500
00:25:03,668 --> 00:25:06,471
No matter what happens to the world,

501
00:25:06,471 --> 00:25:08,706
as long as I'm still here,

502
00:25:09,674 --> 00:25:11,942
I will always be there to catch you.

503
00:25:19,918 --> 00:25:25,524
So, whenever we're in a bad mood,
we'll come here.

504
00:25:25,524 --> 00:25:27,825
Then, face the sea.

505
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:32,129
Close your eyes.

506
00:25:34,399 --> 00:25:35,901
And start counting.

507
00:25:35,901 --> 00:25:39,593
142857.

508
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:45,042
Then slowly open your eyes.

509
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:51,749
And all your worries will disappear.

510
00:25:53,818 --> 00:25:55,886
You remembered.

511
00:26:01,860 --> 00:26:03,661
I've dreamed about it.

512
00:26:09,734 --> 00:26:11,703
That's okay.

513
00:26:11,703 --> 00:26:13,538
Maybe as you keep dreaming,

514
00:26:13,538 --> 00:26:15,607
your memories will become clearer.

515
00:26:15,607 --> 00:26:17,875
Then you'll remember who I am.

516
00:26:20,278 --> 00:26:24,115
Anyway, I believe that
even if memories disappear,

517
00:26:24,115 --> 00:26:26,585
emotions leave an imprint.

518
00:26:26,585 --> 00:26:30,054
Just like how He Xiang Yong
appeared in your dream.

519
00:26:33,592 --> 00:26:35,993
So, you think

520
00:26:36,828 --> 00:26:39,397
my dreams are all emotional imprints?

521
00:26:40,699 --> 00:26:43,468
The fact that you could say those numbers

522
00:26:43,468 --> 00:26:46,036
should be proof enough.

523
00:27:23,642 --> 00:27:25,476
That is...

524
00:27:27,412 --> 00:27:29,580
My sketchbook.

525
00:27:30,315 --> 00:27:32,283
Can I take a look?

526
00:27:34,252 --> 00:27:35,920
Sure.

527
00:28:01,212 --> 00:28:05,650
I don't know why, but when I woke up,

528
00:28:05,650 --> 00:28:09,154
everything related to me had vanished.

529
00:28:09,154 --> 00:28:11,722
Only this sketchbook remained.

530
00:28:47,325 --> 00:28:49,059
What's wrong?

531
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:56,568
A big oval.

532
00:28:56,568 --> 00:28:58,737
With a circle in the middle.

533
00:28:58,737 --> 00:29:00,772
Four boomerangs.

534
00:29:00,772 --> 00:29:01,773
Boomerangs?

535
00:29:01,773 --> 00:29:03,194
Yeah.

536
00:29:04,242 --> 00:29:06,945
And most importantly, a big head.

537
00:29:06,945 --> 00:29:09,252
Big head, small tail.

538
00:29:09,252 --> 00:29:12,683
- Simple, right?
- Big head, small tail.

539
00:29:14,419 --> 00:29:16,086
You...

540
00:29:21,459 --> 00:29:23,427
I don't know why,

541
00:29:24,929 --> 00:29:26,798
but I have this feeling in my heart...

542
00:29:26,798 --> 00:29:30,401
that I want to hug you, and comfort you.

543
00:29:37,442 --> 00:29:39,543
Why?

544
00:29:42,981 --> 00:29:45,416
I'm sorry.

545
00:29:45,416 --> 00:29:48,052
I went to ask Mr. Hua.

546
00:29:48,052 --> 00:29:50,321
He also made a wish,

547
00:29:50,321 --> 00:29:52,856
and he also experiences memory confusion.

548
00:29:58,830 --> 00:30:00,564
Mr. Hua?

549
00:30:03,761 --> 00:30:08,573
[Epilogue]

550
00:30:08,573 --> 00:30:10,774
Xiao You also made a wish?

551
00:30:13,378 --> 00:30:14,879
What do you mean by "also"?

552
00:30:14,879 --> 00:30:17,047
So, someone else made a wish too?

553
00:30:19,951 --> 00:30:22,720
After his wish came true,

554
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:25,223
he never went back to the main island.

555
00:30:25,223 --> 00:30:27,458
He stayed on Starry Islet.

556
00:30:30,361 --> 00:30:33,931
Let these boats carry
my mourning and my apologies.

557
00:30:38,002 --> 00:30:42,640
Mr. Hua, your little patient
would never want you

558
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:45,042
to carry this guilt for the rest of your life.

559
00:30:47,111 --> 00:30:49,447
You were the one who came to me for help,

560
00:30:49,447 --> 00:30:51,482
yet you're the one comforting me.

561
00:30:52,116 --> 00:30:54,118
It's okay.

562
00:30:54,118 --> 00:30:57,856
Some things are easier said than done.

563
00:30:57,856 --> 00:31:00,057
Back to what we were talking about.

564
00:31:00,692 --> 00:31:03,560
By the way, why do I have a feeling lately

565
00:31:04,729 --> 00:31:07,665
this memory is a bit blurry?

566
00:31:07,665 --> 00:31:10,134
It's like a dream,

567
00:31:10,134 --> 00:31:12,603
yet it also feels like it really happened.

568
00:31:14,272 --> 00:31:16,841
Doesn't that make you feel confused?

569
00:31:16,841 --> 00:31:18,376
Which parts are dreams,

570
00:31:18,376 --> 00:31:20,812
and which parts actually happened?

571
00:31:20,812 --> 00:31:22,647
Have you ever heard of cellular memory,

572
00:31:22,647 --> 00:31:24,682
or muscle memory?

573
00:31:26,050 --> 00:31:28,253
The theory is that

574
00:31:28,253 --> 00:31:30,722
memories aren't only stored in the brain.

575
00:31:30,722 --> 00:31:32,289
Right.

576
00:31:34,592 --> 00:31:36,761
Was there a table here before?

577
00:31:36,761 --> 00:31:38,862
Or a cabinet?

578
00:31:39,664 --> 00:31:42,400
Was it always like this?

579
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:44,668
It feels weird.

580
00:31:48,873 --> 00:31:50,742
Why did you make so much jelly?

581
00:31:50,742 --> 00:31:53,378
Didn't you say what's-his-name likes it?

582
00:31:53,378 --> 00:31:55,079
Who?

583
00:31:58,449 --> 00:31:59,850
Who?

584
00:32:01,552 --> 00:32:03,454
That... you know.

585
00:32:05,023 --> 00:32:07,524
How strange. Why can't I remember?

586
00:32:09,060 --> 00:32:10,261
But...

587
00:32:10,261 --> 00:32:11,396
this is still just a hypothesis

588
00:32:11,396 --> 00:32:13,831
that hasn't been scientifically proven.

589
00:32:15,066 --> 00:32:17,401
Why are you more logical than me?

590
00:32:18,002 --> 00:32:19,137
Let me tell you, this jar...

591
00:32:19,137 --> 00:32:21,306
It used to be empty.

592
00:32:21,306 --> 00:32:22,473
I couldn't sleep the other night.

593
00:32:22,473 --> 00:32:24,108
I was going to read a book,

594
00:32:24,108 --> 00:32:25,543
but for some reason,

595
00:32:25,543 --> 00:32:27,078
I started folding paper boats.

596
00:32:27,078 --> 00:32:29,714
I ended up with a whole jar of them.

597
00:32:29,714 --> 00:32:33,151
Then I realized that saying is true.

598
00:32:33,151 --> 00:32:36,420
"The end of science is metaphysics."

599
00:32:38,890 --> 00:32:41,693
I think I've heard that before.

600
00:32:41,693 --> 00:32:44,329
No wonder I felt like
I could find an answer here.

601
00:32:44,329 --> 00:32:46,431
Then you really have heard it.

602
00:32:46,431 --> 00:32:48,099
Instead of letting your brain confuse you,

603
00:32:48,099 --> 00:32:49,500
trust your feelings.

604
00:32:49,500 --> 00:32:51,235
Feel with your heart.

605
00:32:51,235 --> 00:32:53,370
Your heart won't lie to you.

606
00:32:55,206 --> 00:32:56,740
I've got it.

607
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:25,670
Since you chose to abandon He Xiang Yong,

608
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:26,971
he won't be coming back.

609
00:33:26,971 --> 00:33:28,907
Once your wish starts to backfire,
it'll be too late for regrets.

610
00:33:28,907 --> 00:33:29,707
What are you doing?

611
00:33:29,707 --> 00:33:31,876
Hama-chan wants to see the world.

612
00:33:31,876 --> 00:33:33,578
He's signing a contract for an ocean liner.

613
00:33:33,578 --> 00:33:35,646
Put me down!

614
00:33:35,646 --> 00:33:37,315
Have you ever thought
maybe you don't even deserve

615
00:33:37,315 --> 00:33:38,315
to exist in this world?

616
00:33:38,315 --> 00:33:41,080
I need to find He Xiang Yong
so I can be whole again.
